HEADWORD: Sectant
<hw>Sec"tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>secare</ets>, <ets>sectum</ets>, to cut.]</ety> <def>One of the
portions of space bounded by the three coordinate planes. Specif.
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld>, one of the parts of a crystal into which it is
divided by the axial planes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

